PTA Grupp of Estonia to Be Declared Bankrupt, Aeripaeev Reports

-- B y   O t t   U m m e l a s
-- 
2011-09-06T07:55:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-06/pta-grupp-of-estonia-to-be-declared-bankrupt-aeripaeev-reports.html
PTA Grupp AS, an Estonian clothing
maker and retailer, will be declared bankrupt by the Harju
County Court today,  Aeripaeev  reported, citing the chief
executive and a bankruptcy trustee.  The Tallinn-based company is unable to meet its
restructuring plan, Peeter Larin, PTAâ€™s main owner and chief
executive officer, was cited as saying by the newspaper.  PTA has assets worth 844,000 euros ($1.2 million) and
liabilities of 2.9 million euros, according to the newspaper,
citing bankruptcy trustee Urmas Ustav.  Officials at PTA were not immediately available for comment
when reached by phone and e-mail today by Bloomberg News.  To contact the reporters on this story:
